    "search_count": 1,
    "final_answer": "The **Berlin Wall** was built in **1961**. Construction began on **August 13, 1961**, ordered by the government of East Germany (the German Democratic Republic). Its primary purpose was to prevent East German citizens from fleeing to West Berlin and the West. The Wall stood until **November 9, 1989**, when it famously fell during the Peaceful Revolution.",
